verbs.description: depasture (third-person singular simple present depastures, present participle depasturing, simple past and past participle depastured)

entries.meaning: (archaic) To eat up, consume; to strip.
examples: Earth like the patient was whose lively blood / Hath overcome at last some sickness strong, / Whose feeble limbs had been the bait and food / Whereon his strange disease depastur'd long.

entries.meaning: (archaic) To feed or pasture; to graze.
examples: The butter, rich and yellow as the gowaned bank on which the milky mother has depastured, is probably taken directly from the churn.
